
"I can't believe you would disobey your parents like that." Kara's mom said. "All we ever ask, is for a little honesty and respect. But you turn around and do THIS?!"
Kara looked down in disappointment. She knew what she had done was wrong.
"If you want to live in this house, you have to leave." Kara's father said. She knew he was right, he always was. So Kara stood up and looked at the door and nodded to her father.
